---
import { getRelativeLocaleUrl } from "astro:i18n";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

import Base from "../layouts/base.astro";
import NormalBlock from "../components/normal_block.astro";
import ModelSlides from "../components/model_slides.astro";
import Card from "../components/card.astro";

import draping from "../assets/images/photos/draping.jpg";
import colourChart from "../assets/images/photos/colour-chart.jpg";

const link = getRelativeLocaleUrl("en", "colour-interpretation");
---

<Base>
    <article>
        <NormalBlock title="What happens during a colour analysis session?">
            <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">You arrive at the agreed time, and in a comfortable setting, we’ll start with a brief chat
                to understand how I can help you. We’ll go over the basics of colour theory so you know what to expect, and
                you’ll complete a personality quiz to guide us during the draping process. This quiz is not a rulebook but a
                helpful reference to align your personality with the colours that best support your current life phase.</p>
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8 items-center">
                <div>
                    <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">Next, we’ll move on to the practical part: the draping session. You’ll sit without
                        makeup in natural light, with your hair and clothing covered to ensure the focus is entirely on your
                        face. We’ll test various shades – warm and cool, vibrant and soft – to identify which colours enhance
                        your natural glow and which may make you appear tired. This process reveals the shades that make you
                        look youthful, fresh, and authentic, even without makeup.</p>
                    <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">We’ll also determine whether gold or silver suits you better and explore which
                        jewellery and accessories complement your natural beauty. The goal isn’t to impose strict rules on
                        your wardrobe but to give you the freedom to mix and match colours confidently while highlighting
                        your personality.</p>
                </div>
                <Image class="min-h-full md:max-h-[700px] xl:max-h-[560px] object-cover justify-self-center pb-4 md:order-first" src={draping} alt="" />
            </div>
            <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">Throughout the session, we’ll discuss the psychological effects of colours, which can
                significantly influence your mood and emotions. The right colours boost confidence and positively impact
                those around you, supporting both your external appearance and inner well-being.</p>
            <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">At the end of the consultation, you’ll receive tips on integrating your new colours into
                your existing wardrobe. We’ll discuss how to pair them and select pieces that align with your style. These
                new colours will not only enhance your growth journey but also inspire and uplift both you and those around
                you.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="How long does it take?" bgClass="bg-pic-wardrobe">
            <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">A colour analysis consultation takes <strong>120 minutes</strong>.</p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="What is the cost?">
            <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">Colour analysis: <strong>£125</strong></p>
            <p class="mb-3 md:mb-6">Rainbow package (colour analysis + <a class="underline" href={link}>colour interpretation</a>): <strong>£165</strong></p>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="What’s included?" bgClass="bg-pic-dressing-room">
            <ul class="list-image-checkmark-sm md:list-image-checkmark-md list-outside relative left-4 md:left-5 mb-3 md:mb-6">
                <li>Determination of your colour type and discovery of colours beyond your palette that suit you best.</li>
                <li>Practical tips for everyday dressing.</li>
                <li>Advice on how to wear black effectively – if it’s an essential colour for you, I’ll show you how to make it work.</li>
                <li>A colour palette tailored to your type, making shopping decisions easier.</li>
                <!-- <li>An e-book summarising your colour type and its key features for easy reference.</li> -->
                <li>A detailed email summary of the consultation, sent within 48 hours.</li>
                <li>A follow-up consultation three months later to address questions and review how you’ve applied the advice.</li>
                <li>Email support for any urgent questions before the follow-up session.</li>
            </ul>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="FAQs">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-8 items-center">
                <div>
                    <div class="mb-3">
                        <h4>Why should I avoid wearing makeup during the consultation?</h4>
                        <p>We base the analysis on your natural skin tone for the most accurate results. This way, we can see
                            which colours truly enhance your natural glow. You’re welcome to arrive with makeup, as you’ll have
                            the opportunity to remove it at the start of the session – feel free to bring your own products for
                            reapplication afterward. I’ll also share tips, especially for lipsticks.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-3">
                        <h4>Why do you only work in natural light?</h4>
                        <p>Natural light ensures the most accurate results, as artificial lighting can distort colours. Therefore,
                            I conduct consultations exclusively in natural light: between 9 a.m. and 3 p.m. during winter and from
                            9 a.m. to 5 p.m. in spring, summer, and autumn.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-3">
                        <h4>How do I start using my new colour palette?</h4>
                        <p>I’ll email you a summary of the consultation along with an e-book about your colour type. You’ll also
                            have the chance to ask follow-up questions via email and attend a free follow-up session three months
                            later. Don’t rush the process – take your time exploring colours and styles, and you’ll gradually
                            become more confident. We can even incorporate your old favourite colours with small adjustments for
                            a more harmonious look.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="mb-3 md:mb-6">
                        <h4>Do I have to stick only to my colour palette and abandon other colours?</h4>
                        <p>Not at all! The consultation aims to show you the shades that suit you best, but it’s not about
                            restricting your style. I’ll teach you how to incorporate other colour types so they work for you.
                            The ultimate goal is for you to feel confident and authentic in what you wear – and I’m here to
                            help make that happen!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <Image class="min-h-full md:max-h-[500px] object-cover justify-self-center pb-4" src={colourChart} alt="" />
            </div>
        </NormalBlock>
        <NormalBlock title="How can I book a session?" bgClass="bg-pic-jumpers">
